  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust as an accountant by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, several mitigating factors have been taken into consideration. First, the defendant has no prior criminal history. Second, the defendant has shown remorse and a commitment to restitution by already paying back a portion of the embezzled funds. While white-collar crimes involving an abuse of professional trust warrant incarceration to serve as a deterrent, the mitigating circumstances justify a sentence at the lower end of the typical range. Therefore, a sentence of 6 months of incarceration is deemed appropriate and sufficient.",
  "verdict": 6
}
